long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: Gnome-Photos fails to fetch images. After starting to following error is shown in the main window: > The list of photos can't be fetched > 1-762: syntax error, use of undefined variable 'item'
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): $ rpm -q gnome-photos gnome-photos-3.21.90-1.fc25.x86_64
How reproducible: allways
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Start gnome-photos 2. 3.
Actual results: No photos are fetched
Expected results:
Additional info:
Should be fixed by the GNOME 3.21.92 mega-update.
